{"ts":"2026-07-06T23:26:29.415Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"At decades scale the overwhelming majority of a workspace is closed history. Today context assembly either ignores it (losing the recorded knowledge: decisions, learnings, why-nows) or pays full per-item cost to include it. There is no middle representation between 'full item' and 'absent'.\n\nProposal (long horizon, after pm-801d and pm-4k6b): a derived rollup layer, SDK-first.\n- Cluster closed items by natural epoch boundaries (release, epic subtree, time window) into compact summary records: scope, outcome, key decisions/learnings, member-ID list for drill-down.\n- Summaries are DERIVED artifacts, regenerated from source items + history — never mutations of tracked items (no changelog drag, no history noise); stored like other derived indexes (semantic ledger precedent).\n- Context assembly (pm-4k6b knowledge-density signal) and search can return a rollup as a cheap stand-in when the budget cannot afford members, with drill-down via existing get/history.\n- Complements pm-o79o, which handles the DISK/git cost of old data; this handles the TOKEN/context cost. Together they define the aging story for million-item, decades-spanning workspaces.\n\nStart with a spike + design note; the clustering fidelity question (mechanical rollup vs. model-assisted summaries via an extension hook) is explicitly part of the spike."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-5qmm"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Workspace memory tiers: derived rollup summaries of closed-item epochs keep decades-old work queryable in bounded tokens"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":""},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["context","long-horizon","scale"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-06T23:26:29.415Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-06T23:26:29.415Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":720},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"Design note settles derived-artifact placement, regeneration triggers, and invalidation (aligned with the semantic-ledger precedent); prototype generates epoch/epic rollup summaries on a pm-mi2x synthetic workspace; pm context and pm search can surface rollup records as compact stand-ins under a token budget with drill-down IDs to full items; source items and their history streams remain byte-untouched (derived-only guarantee proven by test); regeneration is deterministic for a fixed workspace state; small workspaces skip the tier entirely with zero configuration"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-9rxu"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-4k6b","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-06T23:26:29.415Z"},{"id":"pm-801d","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-06T23:26:29.415Z"},{"id":"pm-o79o","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-06T23:26:29.415Z"},{"id":"pm-pee5","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-06T23:26:29.415Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"5248a94eba48a2fb602cf86bab99124617be0be51a246f7b9369035754ce111a","message":""}
